        Roper started in 1890 in Illinois as Geo. D. Roper Corporation, an appliance and industrial-products
        manufacturer with a long Sears relationship — for decades Sears owned nearly half the company and
        drove the bulk of Roper's production volume. The modern Roper refrigerator brand is the 1988 Whirlpool
        acquisition of the Roper trademark (Whirlpool beat GE in the bidding war), repositioned as Whirlpool's
